        "other_parliamentary_business": [
            {
                "body": "MPs held a debate on road traffic offence victims and the criminal justice system on Tuesday 30 January 2024 in Westminster Hall. The debate was led by Selaine Saxby MP.\nWatch the debate (https://parliamentlive.tv/Event/Index/62d847df-6a3a-4807-866f-b99837a10d41)\nRead a transcript of the debate (https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2024-01-30/debates/24013028000001/VictimsOfRoadTrafficOffencesCriminalJusticeSystem)\nDuring the debate MPs discussed issues including sentencing for road traffic offences and the length of driving bans for people found guilty of road traffic offences.\nWhat is a Westminster Hall debate?\nWestminster Hall is the second chamber of the House of Commons. Westminster Hall debates give MPs an opportunity to raise local and national issues and receive a response from a government minister. Westminster Hall debates are general debates that do not end in a vote. \nFind out more about Westminster Hall debates (https://ukparliament.shorthandstories.com/cet-westminster-hall-debates/index.html?utm_campaign=0124-cet-WHexplainer&utm_medium=email&utm_source=petcom&utm_term=petitioners)\nGet involved in the work of the UK Parliament\nSign up to the Your UK Parliament newsletter (https://parliament.us14.list-manage.com/subscribe?u=098af33234df9814f59fb205f&id=6e29cb1262) for the latest information on how to get involved and make a difference.\n",
